                <head>[From The France, April 30, 1865.]</head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1865-04-30">April 30, 1865</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>All the European governments have hastened to manifest the indignation with which
                    they have heard of the assassination of Mr. Lincoln, and to send to Washington
                    the expression of their grief and sympathy.</p>
                <p>This horrible outrage has provoked similar manifestations in all the parliaments
                    of Europe now sitting at Turin, London and Berlin.</p>
                <p>We have reason to believe that the French chambers will not fail to take part
                    publicly in the expression of that feeling with which the whole country is
                    animated.</p>
            </div>
